p2
VAward for Seshagopalan
p3
sVnews
p4
VMudhra will host its 14th Fine Arts Festival from December 7-11 at the Infosys Hall, Ramakrishna Mission School premises, T. Nagar. There will be a variety of events including vocal and instrumental concerts, jugalbandhis, bhajans, dramas, music lec-\u000adems, a quiz on fine arts, nama sankeertanam, dance recitals and a special music appreciation programme exclusively for rasikas. On the inaugural day, Madurai T. N. Seshagopalan, noted musician, harikatha and veena exponent, will be honoured with the Mudhra Award of Excellence for his outstanding contribution to Carnatic music. The award function will be followed by a violin duet by Mysore Nagaraj and Manjunath. For details, contact 28220453, 98400 72821.
